dd520 | 1 | Joseph addresses Apa Pisentius, probably Bishop of Coptos (569-632 A.D.), who fled from Coptos to western Thebes during the Sassanian invasion of Egypt in the early 7th century.
dd544_n | 1 | Bishop Pisentius' extensive correspondence (only letters addressed to him) circulated on the antiquities market in the 19th century and are mainly held by the Louvre (see Revillout, Eugene. "Textes coptes: Extraits de la correspondence de St. Pesunthius, eveque de Coptos, et de plusiers documents analogues (juridiques ou economiques)." Revue Egyptologique 9 (1900) p. 133-177; 10 (1902) p. 34-47; 14 (1914) p. 22-32.
